    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a museum-grade 1997 Porsche 911 Carrera, the final evolution of the air-cooled flat-six. This example features the 3.6L M64 engine with Varioram induction, ensuring peak volumetric efficiency. The G50/20 manual transaxle offers surgical shift precision, while the Bosch ABS 5.3 and four-piston monoblock calipers provide immense stopping power. The undercarriage is dry, showing no signs of oil migration or heat-cycling fatigue. With its multi-link LSA rear axle and pristine factory geometry, this 993 delivers an uncompromising, visceral driving experience. Truly a concours-level specimen for the serious enthusiast.",
